While researching on #13850 I think I found a logic bug in `FindActorsOnLine `in `WorldExtensions.cs`
.
The bug causes the area off effect of a beam weapon (which uses FindActorsOnLine ) to shrink to zero while aligned with a coordinate axe. This sonic tank fired straight down, only hittig 3 light inf actors exactly on the path. Firing diagonaly however has the intended AOE.
![sonictank](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16046997/29279106-120a17dc-8117-11e7-98fc-7e110f3ece13.png)

I think the bug is caused here: (assume line parallel with y-axis)
```
var xDir = Math.Sign(lineEnd.X - lineStart.X);
var yDir = Math.Sign(lineEnd.Y - lineStart.Y);
```
Math.Sign retuns 0 if lineEnd.X=lineStart.X **!!**   
```
var dir = new WVec(xDir, yDir, 0);
var overselect = dir * (1024 + lineWidth.Length + targetExtraSearchRadius.Length);
			var finalTarget = lineEnd + overselect;
			var finalSource = lineStart - overselect;

var actorsInSquare = world.ActorMap.ActorsInBox(finalTarget, finalSource);
```
..which causes overselect to be 0 on x direction and leads to a box with no width (==line). 

A fix could be to catch case lineEnd.X==lineStart.X before Math.Sign() and set xDir=1.
Same for yDir.
